\subsection{Hierarchy-preserving variants of the prior}
\label{sec:hierarchy-null}

Independent log-uniform draws ignore the hierarchical structure of the SM quark spectrum. We test two hierarchy-preserving variants. Variant~A draws log-mass gaps as multiplicative jitter, $\Delta'_i = \Delta_i \cdot U(0.5, 2.0)$, around the empirical SM gaps; Variant~B draws gaps from an exponential distribution matched to the empirical mean. Each uses $N = 10{,}000$ retained draws through the full $12{,}960$-trial search with full CRunDec.

